<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7888aaa9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s721"><num value="721">§ 721.</num><heading> Short title; “person” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This chapter may be cited as “The Upper Mississippi River National Wildlife and Fish Refuge Act.” The term “person” as used therein includes an individual, partnership, association, or corporation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7888aaaa-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1924-06-07/ch346">June 7, 1924, ch. 346</ref>, §§ 1, 12, <ref href="/us/stat/43/650">43 Stat. 650</ref>, 652; <ref href="/us/pl/105/312/tII/s202/b">Pub. L. 105–312, title II, § 202(b)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-30">Oct. 30, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/2957">112 Stat. 2957</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7888aaab-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7888aaac-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id7888aaad-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section is a combination provision, the first sentence being derived from section 1 and the last from section 12, of act <date date="1924-06-07">June 7, 1924</date>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7888aaae-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1998—<ref href="/us/pl/105/312">Pub. L. 105–312</ref> substituted “National Wildlife” for “Wild Life”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
